parseNestedSObj

public static com.sforce.soap.partner.sobject.SObject parseNestedSObj(org.apache.axis.message.MessageElement[] elements,
                                                                      java.lang.String parentName)
Parses nested SObject out of the MessageElement array for the matching parent name.
For ex. if Contact has lookup to Account and relationship name is "Account", then this call should be done as follows
Sobject accountSobj = parseNestedSObj(contactSobj.get_any(), "Account");

Parameters:
elements - MessageElements from a SObject
parentName - Attribute name whose SObject should be parsed
Returns:
parsed nested SObject instance

parseNestedText

public static java.lang.String parseNestedText(org.apache.axis.message.MessageElement element,
                                               java.lang.String childName)
This method expects that the given MessageElement is holding a relationship SObject. So it returns the value of required attribute from that relationship.

Parameters:
element - relationship MessageElement only
childName - attribute from relationship MessageElement whose value is required
Returns:
Text value from relationship sobject's attribute
